<section>
  <h2>Standards and guidelines</h2>

  <gcds-details details-title="Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG)" class="mb-300">
    <gcds-text>WCAG 2.1 is the international standard for web accessibility. Government of Canada services are required to meet Level AA conformance.</gcds-text>
    <ul class="list-disc mt-200">
      <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/">WCAG 2.1 — W3C Recommendation</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/">WCAG 2.1 Quick Reference</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG22/Understanding/">Understanding WCAG 2.2</a></li>
    </ul>
  </gcds-details>

  <gcds-details details-title="GC Design System" class="mb-300">
    <gcds-text>The GC Design System provides accessible, bilingual components and guidance for building Government of Canada digital products.</gcds-text>
    <ul class="list-disc mt-200">
      <li><a href="https://design-system.canada.ca/">GC Design System documentation</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://design-system.canada.ca/en/components/">Component library</a></li>
    </ul>
  </gcds-details>

  <gcds-details details-title="Canada.ca Content Style Guide" class="mb-300">
    <gcds-text>The official style guide for Government of Canada web content, focused on plain language and clear communication for all audiences.</gcds-text>
    <ul class="list-disc mt-200">
      <li><a href="https://www.canada.ca/en/treasury-board-secretariat/services/government-communications/canada-content-style-guide.html">Content Style Guide — Canada.ca</a></li>
    </ul>
  </gcds-details>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Testing tools</h2>

  <gcds-details details-title="Browser extensions" class="mb-300">
    <gcds-text>These browser-based tools help identify accessibility issues during development and review. They are best used as a starting point — automated tools cannot catch all accessibility issues.</gcds-text>
    <ul class="list-disc mt-200">
      <li><a href="https://www.deque.com/axe/devtools/">axe DevTools — Deque</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://accessibilityinsights.io/">Accessibility Insights — Microsoft</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://wave.webaim.org/extension/">WAVE Evaluation Tool — WebAIM</a></li>
    </ul>
  </gcds-details>

  <gcds-details details-title="Screen readers" class="mb-300">
    <gcds-text>Screen reader testing is essential. No automated tool can fully replicate the experience of a user relying on assistive technology.</gcds-text>
    <ul class="list-disc mt-200">
      <li><a href="https://www.nvaccess.org/download/">NVDA — Windows, free</a></li>
      <li><a href="https://www.freedomscientific.com/products/software/jaws/">JAWS — Windows, paid</a></li>
      <li>VoiceOver — built into macOS and iOS</li>
      <li>TalkBack — built into Android</li>
    </ul>
  </gcds-details>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Document accessibility</h2>

  <gcds-details details-title="Microsoft Office" class="mb-300">
    <gcds-text>All Office applications include a built-in Accessibility Checker. Use it to identify and fix issues before sharing or publishing documents.</gcds-text>
    <ul class="list-disc mt-200">
      <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/office/improve-accessibility-with-the-accessibility-checker-a16f6de0-2f39-4a2b-8bd8-5ad801426c7f">Accessibility Checker — Microsoft Support</a></li>
    </ul>
  </gcds-details>

  <gcds-details details-title="PDF accessibility" class="mb-300">
    <gcds-text>PDF documents must be tagged and structured correctly to be usable with screen readers. Start from an accessible source document whenever possible.</gcds-text>
    <ul class="list-disc mt-200">
      <li><a href="https://helpx.adobe.com/acrobat/using/create-verify-pdf-accessibility.html">Create and verify PDF accessibility — Adobe Acrobat</a></li>
    </ul>
  </gcds-details>
</section>

